            "id": "85150831-ae20-4f6e-a200-cb55309dae0b",
            "name": "Authentication",
            "request": {
                "name": "Authentication",
                "description": {
                    "content": "## Steps need to be followed before using the Wheel Pros APIs\n- Register the **user** account in [Product Data Portal](https://data.wheelpros.com)\n- Once the admin approves the account the one-time password will be sent to the registered email address\n- Update the password in the Product Data Portal Portal\n- Request Wheel Pros for APIs you want to access\n## Using AuthToken to Access the Wheel Pros APIs\n\n- accessToken we get in authorize API is the short living token. We can use this token to access the developer APIs.\n- To access the Wheelpros developer APIs the token needs to be part of the request headers\n\n\n  **Required Headers to access Wheel Pros APIs:**\n\n  Authorization: Bearer AccessToken\n\n**Example CURL for usage for AccessToken**\n```curl\ncurl --location --request GET 'https://dev.api.wheelpros.com/pricing/v1/SKU12345?company=1000' \\\n--header 'Authorization: Bearer g2vwheella6z8jy6prosp1tokenn9test'\n```\n",
                    "type": "text/plain"
                },
                "url": {
                    "path": [
                        "v1",
                        "authorize"
                    ],
                    "host": [
                        "{{baseUrl}}"
                    ],
                    "query": [],
                    "variable": []
                },
                "header": [
                    {
                        "key": "Content-Type",
                        "value": "application/json"
                    },
                    {
                        "key": "Accept",
                        "value": "application/json"
                    }
                ],
                "method": "POST",
                "auth": null,
                "body": {
                    "mode": "raw",
                    "raw": "{\n  \"userName\": \"<string>\",\n  \"password\": \"<string>\"\n}",
                    "options": {
                        "raw": {
                            "language": "json"
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            "response": [
                {
                    "id": "36a63b88-dc66-4737-8c62-8b0c6e9d9513",
